cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with biomedical image segmentation using U-net, a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a post-processing technique to improve segmentation accuracy, which involves thresholding and averaging, indicating a focus on machine learning and optimization. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with biomedical images, indicating a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
